## 4. Common Integration Approaches (Legacy 18.2)

| Approach                               | Mechanism                                      | Pros                                          | Cons                                                 |
|----------------------------------------|-----------------------------------------------|-----------------------------------------------|------------------------------------------------------|
| XML SDK (recommended)                  | COM + JBXML requests via `JBRequestProcessor` | Uses JobBOSS logic, supported, upgrade‑safer  | COM‑only, strict XML schema, no direct PO AddRq      |
| Direct SQL (read‑only)                 | Query SQL Server tables                       | Great for triggers/reporting                  | Cannot safely create POs                             |
| Direct SQL (write – not recommended)   | Insert into PO tables                         | Max control                                   | Unsupported, fragile, easy to break rules/upgrades   |
| File‑based imports (if available)      | CSV → JobBOSS import utilities                | Simple, tool‑agnostic                         | Batch‑oriented, limited error feedback               |
| Third‑party/middleware (e.g., quoting) | External app talks to JobBOSS via SDK/other   | Offloads complexity                           | Less granular control, extra licensing/dependency    |

